This paper involves natural language processing techniques such as distributed vector representations and dependency parsing, which are commonly used in the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of machine learning algorithms for automated extraction of line list features also falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques for extracting relevant information from open source reports, which falls under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with public health surveillance, which can be considered a sub-topic of social and information networks (cs.SI).
